            Hedge fund favorites
            <a
              href="https://www.hedgeweek.com/top-hedge-fund-stock-picks-trailed-sp500-in-q3/"
              target="_blank"
              >underperformed</a
            >
            the S&P 500 in Q3. While the top 20 most widely held stocks by hedge
            funds saw a 3.4% gain, the S&P 500 outpaced them with a 5.2%
            increase. Even tech giants like Amazon and Microsoft struggled, both
            falling nearly 9% in the quarter. However, some non-tech stocks like
            UnitedHealth Group and Berkshire Hathaway delivered double-digit
            returns, showing that hedge funds are diversifying beyond tech.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
